org.concordion.ext.excel.conversion

Interface ConversionStrategy<X>

  • Type Parameters:
    X -
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SheetConversionStrategy, WorkbookConversionStrategy
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConversionStrategy, BasicCellConversionStrategy, BasicSheetConversionStrategy, BasicTableStrategy, BasicWorkbookConversionStrategy, DefaultCommentConverter, DefaultStyleConverter, MergedCellConversionStrategy, ParagraphRowStrategy, ParagraphsAndTablesRowStrategy, TableCellConversionStrategy

    public interface ConversionStrategy<X>
    Defines all or part of the approach of converting from X into a HTML String. The contract of this class is that the methods must be called in order: start, process*, end. They must also always be called with the same HTMLBuilder argument. The converter is not thread-safe, but can be reused multiple times serially.
